1977 to 30 June 1978. United finished in third place, securing [[UEFA Cup]] football for the following season.\n\n==Match results==\nDundee United played a total of 50 competitive matches during the 1977\u201378 season.<ref name=\"results\">{{cite web|url=http://www.arabarchive.co.uk/matches.php?|title=Match results 1977/1978|work=Arab Archive|accessdate=7 February 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Legend===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n|- bgcolor = \"#d0ffe3\"\n|<small>Win</small>\n|- bgcolor = \"#f3f3f3\"\n|<small>Draw</small>\n|- bgcolor = \"#ffd0e3\"\n|<small>Loss</small>\n|}\n\nAll results are written with Dundee United's score first.\nOwn goals in italics\n\n===Premier Division===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:95%; text-align:center\"\n|-\n!Date!!Opponent!!Venue!!Result!!Attendance!!Scorers\n|- bgcolor = \"#f3f3f3\"\n|13 August 1977||[[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]]||[[Celtic Park|A]]||0-0||33,159||\n|- bgcolor = \"#d0ffe3\"\n|20 August 1977||[[St Mirren F.C.|St Mirren]]||[[Tannadice Park|H]]||2-1||7,658||[[Gordon Wallace (footballer, born 1943)|Wallace]], [[Derek Addison|Addison]]\n|- bgcolor = \"#f3f3f3\"\n|27 August 1977||[[Aberdeen F.C.|Aberdeen]]||[[Pittodrie Stadium|A]]||0-0||17,082||\n|- bgcolor = \"#ffd0e3\"\n|10 September 1977||[[Hibernian F.C.|Hibernian]]||[[Tannadice Park|H]]||2-0||6,518||[[Billy Kirkwood|Kirkwood]], [[Andy Rolland|Rolland]] (penalty)\n|- bgcolor = \"#d0ffe3\"\n|17 September 1977||[[Clydebank F.C.|Clydebank]]||[[Kilbowie Park|A]]||3-0||2,853||[[Paul Sturrock|Sturrock]], [[John Bourke (footballer)|Bourke]], [[George Fleming (footballer born 1948)|Fleming]]\n|- bgcolor = \"#d0ffe3\"\n|24 September 1977||[[Motherwell F.C.|Motherwell]]||[[Tannadice Park|H]]||3-1||7,810||[[George Fleming (footballer born 1948)|Fleming]], [[Paul Sturrock|Sturrock]], [[John Bourke (footballer)|Bourke]]\n|- bgcolor = \"#d0ffe3\"\n|1 October 1977||[[Ayr United F.C.|Ayr United]]||[[Somerset Park|A]]||2-0||3,281||[[Paul Hegarty|Hegarty]], ''[[Alex McAnespie|McAnes