ted_F.C._season"}
{"title_page": "Dundee derby", "text_new": "{{use dmy dates|date=July 2013}}\n{{use British English|date=March 2013}}\n{{Infobox sports rivalry\n| name                     = Dundee Derby\n| other names              = <!-- Other names or references to Derby -->\n| image                    = [[File:Dundee Derby Kits.svg]]\n| city or region           = [[Dundee]], Scotland\n| first contested          = \n| teams involved           = [[Dundee F.C.]]<br>[[Dundee United F.C.]]\n| most wins                = Dundee United (80)\n| most player appearances  = \n| mostrecent               = Dundee United 1\u20131 Dundee<br>{{nowrap|[[2019\u201320 Scottish Championship]]}}<br><small>(27 December 2019)</small>\n| nextmeeting              = ''To be confirmed''<ref>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/51858736 Coronavirus: Scottish football postponed until further notice], BBC Sport, 13 March 2020</ref>\n| total                    = 171\n| league                   = \n| series                   = '''Dundee United''': 80<br>'''Draw''': 42<br>'''Dundee''': 49\n| regularseason            = \n| postseason               = \n| largestvictory = Dundee 5 - 0 Dundee United <br>[[Scottish Division One]]<br><small>(28 August 1926)</small> <br> Dundee 0 - 5 Dundee United <br>[[Scottish Division One]]<br><small>(11 September 1965)</small>\n| smallestvictory          =\n| broadcasters             = \n| stadiums                 = [[Dens Park]]<small> (Dundee FC)</small><br>[[Tannadice Park]]<small> (Dundee United)</small>\n| map_location             = \n| map_label1               = \n| map_label1_position      = \n| map_label2               = \n| coordinates1             =\n| coordinates2             =\n}}\n\nThe '''Dundee derby''' is a [[Football (soccer)|football]] match between [[Dundee F.C.|Dundee]] and [[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]]. The clubs are based yards apart in the city of [[Dundee]], the fourth-largest city in [[Scotland]].\n\n==History==\n[[File:Map of Dens Park and Tannadice Park, Dundee, Scotland, October 2010.jpg|thumb|left|Map showing the proximity of [[Tannadice Park]] home Dundee United (right) to Dundee FC's stadium [[Dens Park]] (left)]]\nDundee is the older of the two, having been founded in 1893, compared to Dundee United which was founded in 1909 as Dundee Hibernian following the demise of [[Dundee Harp]], a club founded by Irish immigrants in 1879. While United's origins stem from [[Irish migration to Great Britain#Irish in Scotland|Irish immigration]], the rivalry is not sectarian in the manner of the [[Old Firm]].\n\nDundee had long been the more successful club, playing more seasons in the top flight than their rivals and winning one League title, one Scottish Cup and three League Cups before United lifted a major trophy. However, from the 1970s under [[Jim McLean]] the tide turned in the city's footballing rivalry. United would go on to be a major force in Scottish football in the 1980s, winning their first three major honours at [[Dens Park]] including a League Cup win against Dundee in [[1980\u201381 Scottish League Cup|1980]]; the 1983 league title was also won there. Their rivalry with [[Aberdeen F.C.|Aberdeen]], who also lifted several trophies during the period, was entitled the [[New Firm (Scotland)|New Firm]]. In [[1993\u201394 Scottish Cup|1994]] United won their first Scottish Cup, and their second in [[2009\u201310 Scottish Cup|2010]], in doing so drawing level with Dundee on five major trophies won.\n\n[[File:Dundee football grounds from Dundee Law, November 2014.jpg|thumb|right|300px|view from [[Dundee Law]] over the two grounds, 2014]] \nThe two grounds are the closest League grounds in Britain and with it a unique rivalry has developed, though one often deemed more amicable than most, similar to the [[Merseyside derby]], [[Derby della Madonnina]] in [[Milan]], and the [[Derby della Lanterna]] of [[Genoa]] with many families split down the middle in support.{{citation needed|date=February 2018}}\n\nThe two clubs even had a combined [[Football hooliganism|hooligan 'firm']], known as the Dundee Utility, which was formed to stand up to the larger firms of the Glasgow and Edinburgh clubs.<ref name=\"sundayherald050508\">{{cite news |last=Didcock |first=Barry |title=Casuals: The Lost Tribe of Britain |publisher=[[Sunday Herald]] |date=8 May 2005 |url=http://www.findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_qn4156/is_20050508/ai_n14624276 |accessdate=12 February 2018 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090924000604/http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_qn4156/is_20050508/ai_n14624276/pg_3/ |archivedate=24 September 2009 }}</ref>\n\n==Statistics==\n===Domestic head-to-head===\n\nIn domestic head-to-head matches, United are quite far in front; the teams have played each other 170 times, Dundee United winning 80 compared to Dundee's 49. A total of 41 matches have ended in a stalemate.<ref name=\"domestic\">{{cite web|url=http://www.soccerbase.com/head2.sd?team2id=740&team1id=737|title=All time results between Dundee and Dundee United|accessdate=2008-02-18|publisher=Soccerbase}}</ref> Dundee United have won more league, [[Scottish Cup]] and [[Scottish League Cup|League Cup]] matches.\n\n{{updated|27 December 2019}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:95%; text-align:center\"\n|-\n! Team !! League !! Scottish Cup !! League Cup !! '''Total'''\n|-\n| {{left}}[[Dundee F.C.]] || 41 || 3 || 5 || bgcolor=\"00008B\" |<center><span style=\"color:white;\">'''49'''</span></center>\n|-\n| {{left}}[[Dundee United F.C.]] || 65 || 8 || 7 ||bgcolor=FF7700|<center><span style=\"color:black;\">'''80'''</span></center>\n|-\n| {{left}}Draw || 31 || 7 || 4 || '''42'''\n|}\n\n===League competition===\n\nDundee have competed in more seasons of top flight football with 93 in total to United's 58, but United have maintained a better points to game average in the top tier. Both clubs have won the [[list of Scottish football champions|Scottish league championship]] once, Dundee in [[1961\u201362 Scottish Division One|1962]] and United in [[1982\u201383 Scottish Premier Division|1983]]. The clubs also sometimes meet in league games outside the top tier, as in [[1995&ndash;96 in Scottish football|1995&ndash;96]] and [[2019&ndash;20 in Scottish football|2019&ndash;20]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/48424403 |title=Dundee & Dundee United's plight 'sad' for city, says Jim McInally |work= |publisher=BBC Sport |date=27 May 2019 |accessdate=28 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n'''All-time top flight table (1890/91-present \u2013 124th Season)'''\n\n:''As of 27 October 2019:''\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size:95%\"\n|-\n!Club\n!Seasons\n!Played\n!W\n!D\n!L\n!GF\n!GA\n!GD\n!Pts\n!Pts avg\n!Win%\n!Champions\n!2nd\n!3rd\n!4th\n|-\n|{{left}}[[Dundee F.C.|Dundee]]||bgcolor=00008B|<center><span style=\"color:white;\">'''97'''</span></center>||3302||1248||744||1310||5084||5146||\u221262||4488||'''1.36'''||'''37.80'''||style=\"background:gold;\"|1|| style=\"background:silver;\"|4|| style=\"background:#cd7f32;\"|1||7\n|-\n|{{left}}[[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]]||bgcolor=FF7700|<center><span style=\"color:black;\">'''59'''</span></center>||2174||820||559||795||3171||3155||16||3016||'''1.39'''|| '''37.72'''|| style=\"background:gold;\"|1||-|| style=\"background:#cd7f32;\"|8||12\n|}\n\n'''Scottish Premiership Table (2013/14\u2013present \u2013 7th Season)'''\n\n:''As of 27 October 2019:''\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size:95%\"\n|-\n!Club\n!Seasons\n!Played\n!W\n!D\n!L\n!GF\n!GA\n!GD\n!Pts\n!Pts avg\n!Win%\n!Champions\n!2nd\n!3rd\n!4th\n|-\n|{{left}}[[Dundee F.C.|Dundee]]||bgcolor=00008B|<center><span style=\"color:white;\">'''5'''</span></center>||190||48||46||96||204||311||\u2212107||190||'''1'''||'''25.26'''||-||-||-||-\n|-\n|{{left}}[[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]]||bgcolor=FF7700|<center><span style=\"color:black;\">'''3'''</span></center>||114||41||22||51||168