\"|1||7\n|-\n|{{left}}[[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]]||bgcolor=FF7700|<center><span style=\"color:black;\">'''19'''</span></center>||662||253||141||268||1139||1250||\u2212111||900||'''1.36'''|| '''38.22'''||-||-||-||1\n|}\n\n===Cup competition===\n====Scottish Cup (1873/74-present \u2013 135th Season)====\nIn the [[Scottish Cup]], Dundee have competed in 108 tournaments, reaching 5 cup finals. They were cup winners in [[1909\u201310 Scottish Cup|1910]] as well as runners-up in [[1924\u201325 Scottish Cup|1925]], [[1951\u201352 Scottish Cup|1952]], [[1963\u201364 Scottish Cup|1964]] and [[2002\u201303 Scottish Cup|2003]]. Dundee United have competed in 88 tournaments, reaching twice as many cup finals as Dundee. They were cup winners in [[1993\u201394 Scottish Cup|1994]] and [[2009\u201310 Scottish Cup|2010]] as well as runners up in [[1973\u201374 Scottish Cup|1974]], [[1980\u201381 Scottish Cup|1981]], [[1984\u201385 Scottish Cup|1985]], [[1986\u201387 Scottish Cup|1987]], [[1987\u201388 Scottish Cup|1988]], [[1990\u201391 Scottish Cup|1991]] (being unable to secure that trophy in six finals under otherwise successful boss [[Jim McLean]]), [[2004\u201305 Scottish Cup|2005]] and [[2013\u201314 Scottish Cup|2014]].\n\n:''As of 27 October 2019:''\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size:95%\"\n|-\n!Club\n!Seasons\n!Played\n!W\n!D\n!L\n!GF\n!GA\n!GD\n!Win%\n!Winners\n!Runner-up\n!Semi Final\n!Quarters\n|-\n|{{left}}[[Dundee F.C.|Dundee]]||bgcolor=00008B|<center><span style=\"color:white;\">'''113'''</span></center>||359||157||92||110||622||421||201||'''43.73'''|| style=\"background:gold;\"|1|| style=\"background:silver;\"|4||13||17\n|-\n|{{left}}[[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]]||bgcolor=FF7700|<center><span style=\"color:black;\">'''93'''</span></center>||301||139||71||91||545||419||126||'''46.18'''|| style=\"background:gold;\"|2|| style=\"background:silver;\"|8||11||14\n|}\n\n====League Cup (1946/47-present \u2013 74th Season)====\nIn the [[Scottish League Cup|League Cup]], Dundee have been the winners on three occasions, in [[1951\u201352 Scottish League Cup|1951\u201352]], [[1952\u201353 Scottish League Cup|1952\u201353]] and [[1973\u201374 Scottish League Cup|1973\u201374]], they were also runners-up in [[1967\u201368 Scottish League Cup|1967\u201368]], [[1980\u201381 Scottish League Cup|1980\u201381]] and [[1995\u201396 Scottish League Cup|1995\u201396]]. Dundee United meanwhile have won it twice, in [[1979\u201380 Scottish League Cup|1979\u201380]] and [[1980\u201381 Scottish League Cup|1980\u201381]], and were runners-up in [[1981\u201382 Scottish League Cup|1981\u201382]], [[1984\u201385 Scottish League Cup|1984\u201385]], [[1997\u201398 Scottish League Cup|1997\u201398]], [[2007\u201308 Scottish League Cup|2007\u201308]], and [[2015 Scottish League Cup Final|2014\u201315]] (losing to either [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]] or [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]] on every occasion).\n\n:''As of 27 October 2019:''\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size:95%\"\n|-\n!Club\n!Seasons\n!Played\n!W\n!D\n!L\n!GF\n!GA\n!GD\n!Win%\n!Winners\n!Runner-up\n!Semi Final\n!Quarters\n|-\n|{{left}}[[Dundee F.C.|Dundee]]||bgcolor=00008B|<center><span style=\"color:white;\">'''74'''</span></center>||361||180||59||122||710||513||197||'''49.86'''|| style=\"background:gold;\"|3|| style=\"background:silver;\"|3||6||12\n|-\n|{{left}}[[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]]||bgcolor=FF7700|<center><span style=\"color:black;\">'''74'''</span></center>||381||195||56||130||731||576||155||'''51.18'''|| style=\"background:gold;\"|2|| style=\"background:silver;\"|5||12||16\n|}\n\n===European competition===\nIn European competition, [[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]] have played in more tournaments and in more games, competing in 26 tournaments to [[Dundee F.C.|Dundee]]'s 7, and playing in 78 more matches.<ref name=\"euro\">{{cite web|url=http://uk.geocities.com/scottishfootballineurope/allscores.htm|title=Scottish Football in Europe|accessdate=2008-02-18|publisher=Scottish Football in Europe|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071029204644/http://uk.geocities.com/scottishfootballineurope/allscores.htm|archivedate=29 October 2007}}</ref> Neither side has won a trophy, although United were runners-up in the [[UEFA Cup 1986\u201387|1986\u201387 UEFA Cup]]; both sides have reached the semi-finals of the [[UEFA Champions League|European Cup]] once.\n\n:''As of 9 August 2012:''\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:95%; text-align:center\"\n|-\n! Team !! T !! P !! W !! D !! L !! F !! A\n|-\n| {{left}}[[Dundee F.C.|Dundee]] ||bgcolor=00008B|<center><span style=\"color:white;\"> '''7''' </span></center>|| 32 || 16 || 2 || 14 || 61 || 48\n|-\n| {{left}}[[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]] ||bgcolor=FF7700|<center><span style=\"color:black;\"> '''26''' </span></center>|| 110 || 46 || 30 || 34 || 168 || 116\n|}\n\n===Trophy cabinet comparison===\nBoth clubs have won 5 major Scottish football trophies.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 13px; width:95%;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:8%;\"| Club  \n! colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:24%;\"| League Champions\n! colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:24%;\"| Scottish Cup Winners\n! colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:24%;\"| League Cup Winners\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:6%;\"| Total\n|-\n! style=\"width:4%;\"| Total\n! style=\"width:20%;\"| Seasons\n! style=\"width:4%;\"| Total\n! style=\"width:20%;\"| Seasons\n! style=\"width:4%;\"| Total\n! style=\"width:20%;\"| Seasons\n|-\n| {{left}} [[Dundee F.C.|Dundee]]\n| bgcolor=00008B|<center><span style=\"color:white;\">'''1'''</span></center>\n| {{left}}1961\u201362\n| bgcolor=00008B|<center><span style=\"color:white;\">'''1'''</span></center>\n| {{left}}1909\u201310\n| bgcolor=00008B|<center><span style=\"color:white;\">'''3'''</span></center>\n| {{left}}1951\u201352, 1952\u201353, 1973\u201374\n| bgcolor=00008B|<center><span style=\"color:white;\">'''5'''</span></center>\n|-\n| {{left}}[[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]]\n| bgcolor=FF7700|<center><span style=\"color:black;\">'''1'''</span></center>\n| {{left}}1982\u201383\n| bgcolor=FF7700|<center><span style=\"color:black;\">'''2'''</span></center>\n| {{left}}1993\u201394, 2009\u201310\n| bgcolor=FF7700|<center><span style=\"color:black;\">'''2'''</span></center>\n| {{left}}1979\u201380, 1980\u201381 \n| bgcolor=FF7700|<center><span style=\"color:black;\">'''5'''</span></center>\n|}\n\n==Team records==\n\nThe following are records just for the Dundee derby itself:\n* The longest unbeaten run in all matches is 13, held by United, this was between December 1979 and September 1983, 11 of these were Wins.\n* The longest unbeaten run in home matches is held by Dundee when United failed to beat them for 14 games between November 1925 and August 1962.\n* The longest unbeaten run in away matches is held by United with a 12 match run at Dens Park between April 1963 and April 1971 which included 8 victories.\n* The longest unbroken winning run in all matches belongs to United with 7 between March 1988 and April 1989.\n* The longest unbroken winning run at home belongs to United with 6 between September 1974 and September 1981.\n* The longest unbroken winning run away from home belongs to United who scored 8 consecutive victories at Dens Park between December 1980 and November 1984.\n* The record home victory in a league match is 5\u20130 recorded by Dundee at Dens Park in August 1926\n* The record away victory in a league match is 5\u20130 recorded by United at Dens Park in September 1965.\n* The highest scoring match was in September 1971 when Dundee won 6\u20134 at Dens Park.\n* Paul Sturrock of United holds the mark for the most derby goals with 14, 2 of these came in United's 3\u20130 League Cup Final win over Dundee at Dens Park in December 1980.\n* Record Attendance:\n** 29,106 at Dens Park, 14 May 1983 (Premier Division)                                                                                                          \n** 21,325 at Tannadice, 3 January 1966 (old Division One)\n* Lowest Attendance:\n** 9,185 at Tannadice, 12 December 1999 (SPL)                                                                        \n** 7,645 at Dens Park, 29 January 1994 (Premier Division)\n\n==Players at both clubs==\n[[File:Scott Robertson dundee.jpg|thumb|left|180px|[[Dundee]]-born [[Scott Robertson (footballer born 1985)|Scott Robertson]] began his career at [[Dens Park]] then switched to [[Tannadice]], making over 100 appearances for both clubs]] \nFourteen players have signed for Dundee United directly from Dundee with eight making the opposite journey from [[Tannadice Park|Tannadice]] to [[Dens Park]]. Only players who have played at least one first team game for both clubs are currently included.\n\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Dundee to Dundee United===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:95%\"\n|-\n! Date\n! Player\n! Fee\n|-\n| {{0}}{{0}} {{0}}{{0}}{{0}} 1909 || {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Tim Dailly]] || ''Unknown''<ref name=\"history\">{{cite web|publisher=Dundee United F.C.|accessdate=2008-02-18|url=http://www.dundeeunitedfc.co.uk/index.asp?pg=238|title=Dundee United A to Z (D)|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080410204548/http://www.dundeeunitedfc.co.uk/index.asp?pg=238|archivedate=10 April 2008|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{0}}{{0}} {{0}}{{0}}{{0}} 1909 || {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Thomas Flood (footballer)|Thomas Flood]] || ''Unknown''<ref name=\"history\"/>\n|-\n| {{0}}{{0}} {{0}}{{0}}{{0}} 1913 || {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Collie Martin]] || ''Unknown''<ref name=\"history\"/>\n|-\n| {{0}}{{0}} {{0}}{{0}}{{0}} 1913 || {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Fred Stoessell]] || ''Unknown''<ref name=\"history\"/>\n|-\n| {{0}}{{0}} {{0}}{{0}}{{0}} 1933 || {{flagicon|SCO}} [[James Angus Munro]] || ''Unknown''<ref name=\"history\"/>\n|-\n| {{0}}{{0}} {{0}}{{0}}{{0}} 1947 || {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Jimmy Dickson]] || ''Unknown''<ref na