{"title_page": "Ridiculousness (TV series)", "text_new": "{{short description|American comedy TV series}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Ridiculousness\n| image                    = Ridiculousness (TV series).jpg\n| genre                    = {{plainlist|\n* [[Clip show]]\n* [[Comedy]]\n}}\n| presenter                = {{plainlist|\n* [[Rob Dyrdek]]\n* [[Steelo Brim|Sterling \"Steelo\" Brim]]\n* [[Chanel West Coast]]\n}}  \n| theme_music_composer     = [[Mark Mothersbaugh]]\n| opentheme                = {{plainlist|\n* \"[[Uncontrollable Urge]]\"\n* created by [[Devo]]; performed by Rob Dyrdek\n}}\n| country                  = United States\n| language                 = English\n| num_seasons              = 17\n| num_episodes             = 492\n| list_episodes            = List of Ridiculousness episodes\n| executive_producer       = {{plainlist|\n* Christian Duguay\n* [[Jeff Tremaine]]\n* Kristina Edwards\n* Lauren Dolgen\n* Michelle Klepper\n* Rob Dyrdek\n* Sara Cohen\n* Shane Nickerson\n}}\n| runtime                  = 22 minutes\n| company                  = {{plainlist|\n* Superjacket Productions (2014\u2013present)\n* Gorilla Flicks (2014\u2013present)\n* Dickhouse Productions (2011\u20132014)\n}}\n| distributor              = [[CBS Television Distribution]]\n| picture_format           = {{plainlist|\n* [[480i]] ([[Standard-definition television|SDTV]])\n* [[1080i]] ([[High-definition television|HDTV]])\n}}\n| first_aired              = {{Start date|2011|8|29}}\n| last_aired               = present\n| website                  = http://www.mtv.com/shows/ridiculousness/series.jhtml\n| channel                  = [[MTV]], [[MTV2]]\n| related              = ''[[Amazingness]]''\n}}\n\n'''''Ridiculousness''''' is an American [[comedy]] [[clip show]] that began airing on August 29, 2011. It is hosted by [[Rob Dyrdek]] and co-hosted by [[Steelo Brim|Sterling \"Steelo\" Brim]] and [[Chanel West Coast]]. ''Ridiculousness'' strictly showcases various [[viral video]]s from the Internet, usually involving failed do-it-yourself attempts at stunts, to which Rob and his panelists add mock commentary.\n\n==Production==\n\nOn September 10, 2012, ''Ridiculousness'' was renewed for a twenty episode third season.<ref>{{cite web|last=Patten|first=Dominic|title=MTV Renews \u2018Ridiculousness\u2019 For Third Season|url=https://www.deadline.com/2012/09/mtv-renews-ridiculousness-for-third-season/|work=Deadline Hollywood|date=September 10, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2012/09/10/mtv-renews-ridiculousness-for-a-third-season/148055/|title='Ridiculousness' Renewed by MTV For a Third Season|last=Kondology|first=Amanda|publisher=TV By the Numbers|date=September 10, 2012|accessdate=January 17, 2013}}</ref> It premiered on February 14, 2013,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2013/01/17/ridiculousness-returns-february-14-at-10pm/165728/|title='Ridiculousness' Returns February 14 at 10PM|last=Kondology|first=Amanda|publisher=TV By the Numbers|date=January 17, 2013|accessdate=January 17, 2013}}</ref> and included a crossover with ''[[Jersey Shore (TV series)|Jersey Shore]]'' when [[Pauly D]] guest-starred. The season would later go into hiatus in April 2013 and return on July 18, 2013.<ref>{{cite web|last=Kondolojy|first=Amanda|title=MTV is Heating Up This Summer With the Return of Rob Drydek's 'Ridiculousness', 'Money From Strangers' and 'Nikki & Sara Live'|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2013/06/20/mtv-is-heating-up-this-summer-with-the-return-of-rob-drydeks-ridiculousness-money-from-strangers-and-nikki-sara-live/188266/|work=TV by the Numbers|date=June 20, 2013}}</ref> Season 3 averaged a 1.6 P12-34 rating and is the No.1 original cable series in its time slot with P12-34.<ref name=s4renew>{{cite press release|last=Bibel|first=Sara|title='Ridiculousness' Renewed for Season 4 & 'Rob Dyrdek's Fantasy Factory' Renewed for Season 6 by MTV|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2013/09/17/ridiculousness-renewed-for-season-4-rob-dyrdeks-fantasy-factory-renewed-for-season-6-by-mtv/203166/|work=TV by the Numbers|date=September 17, 2013}}</ref>\n\nAs of October 2015, some episodes of ''Ridiculousness'' were repackaged due to the series being consistently [[marathon (media)|marathoned]] on MTV and MTV2, with lower-cost [[production music]] under blanket licenses overlaying the former tracks which would have required MTV to pay [[music licensing]] fees to artists, as Viacom forced a number of budget cuts on their networks due to ratings issues.\n\nThe series is produced by Superjacket Productions, Rob Dyrdek's production company, under a multi-year deal with MTV.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2014/06/25/rob-dyrdek-and-his-production-company-super-jacket-sign-multi-year-deal-with-mtv-785015/20140625mtv02/|title=Breaking News - Rob Dyrdek and His Production Company Super Jacket Sign Multi-Year Deal with MTV {{!}} TheFutonCritic.com|website=www.thefutoncritic.com|access-date=2017-04-26}}</ref>\n\n==Episodes==\n{{main article|List of Ridiculousness episodes}}\n{{:List of Ridiculousness episodes}}\n== Reception==\n[[David Wiegand]] of the ''[[San Francisco Chronicle]]'' wrote: \"The best thing about watching (viral videos) online is that you don't have to listen to Dyrdek's patter or the stellar contributions of his guests... the bigger danger is in watching the show in the first place: You might die of boredom. In other words, don't try this at home.\"<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.sfgate.com/news/article/Ridiculousness-review-silly-and-boring-for-MTV-2334021.php |title= 'Ridiculousness' review: silly and boring for MTV |last1=Wiegand |first1=David |date= August 26, 2011 |website= www.sfgate.com |publisher= SF Gate|access-date= November 8, 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, a ''[[New York Times]]'' study of the 50 TV shows with the most [[Facebook Like]]s found that ''Ridiculousness'' \"is most popular in rural Alaska, New Mexico and Montana, and least popular in Washington D.C., Atlanta and San Francisco\".<ref name=\"katz201612,k27\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2016/12/26/upshot/duck-dynasty-vs-modern-family-television-maps.html |title=\u2018Duck Dynasty\u2019 vs. \u2018Modern Family\u2019: 50 Maps of the U.S. Cultural Divide |last=Katz |first=Josh |date=2016-12-27 |newspaper=The New York Times}}</ref>\n\n==International versions==\nThe program was very successful internationally, which eventually led to the creation of localized versions in some regions. These versions are hosted by local celebrities in their respective regions and is broadcast on international MTV networks, alongside the original U.S version, or on other selected channels.\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders unsortable\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:115px;\"| Country\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:120px;\"| Channel\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:100;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:85px;\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:75px;\"| Reference\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{Flag|Chile}}\n| [[Canal 13 (Chile)|Canal 13]]\n| ''Rid\u00edculos Chile''\n| 2015\u2013\n|<ref>{{cite web|author=|title=Rid\u00edculos Chile - 13.cl|url=http://www.13.cl/programas/ridiculos-chile|work=13.cl|date=}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{Flag|France}}\n| [[MTV France]]\n| ''Ridiculous Made In France''\n|rowspan=8| 2016\u2013\n|<ref>{{cite web|author=|title=Ridiculous Made in France : Les pr\u00e9sentateurs sont... - MTV France|url=http://www.mtv.fr/news/ridiculous-made-in-france-les-presentateurs-sont/knl1eo|work=www.mtv.fr|date=}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{Flag|Spain}}\n| [[MTV Spain]]\n| ''[[Verg\u00fcenza Ajena: Made in Spain]]''\n|<ref>{{cite web|author=|title=Verg\u00fcenza Ajena Made in Spain -  Programa - MTV Espa\u00f1a|url=http://www.mtv.es/programas/verguenza-ajena-made-in-spain/d6j7np|work=www.mtv.es|date=}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{Flag|Brazil}}\n| [[MTV (Brazil)]]\n| ''Rid\u00edculos MTV''\n|<ref>{{cite web|author=|title=Rid\u00edculos -  Programa de TV - MTV Brasil|url=http://www.mtv.com.br/programas/l96n08/ridiculos|work=MTV Brasil|date=}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{Flag|South Africa}}\n| [[MTV]](Simulcasts on [[MTV Base (Africa)|MTV Base Africa]])\n| ''Ridiculousness \u00c1frica''\n|<ref>{{cite web|author=|title=Ridiculousness is coming to Africa! and these are your hosts\u2026 - MTV South Africa|url=http://www.mtv.co.za/news/ridiculousness-coming-to-africa-these-are-the-hosts/rcmrit|work=www.mtv.co.za|date=}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{Flag|Mexico}}\n| [[MTV (Latin America)]]\n| ''Rid\u00edculos MTV''\n|<ref>{{cite web|author=|title=Rid\u00edculos MTV - MTV America Latina|url=http://www.mtvla.com/mx/ridiculos-mtv|work=mtvla.com|date=}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{Flag|Sweden}}\n| [[MTV Sweden]]\n| ''Ridiculousness Sverige''\n|<ref>{{cite web|author=|title=Ridiculousness Sverige - Shows - MTV|url=http://m.mtv.se/program/3108-ridiculousness-sverige|work=m.mtv.se|date=}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{Flag|Poland}}\n| [[MTV Poland]]\n| ''[[Niemo\u017cliwe Made In Poland]]''\n|<ref>{{cite web|author=|title=Niemo\u017cliwe PL - Shows - MTV|url=http://m.mtv.pl/wideo/3110-niemozliwe-pl|work=m.mtv.pl|date=}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{Flag|Netherlands}}<br>{{Flag|Belgium}}\n| [[MTV Netherlands]]\n| ''Dutch Ridiculousness''\n|<ref>{{cite web|author=|title=Dutch Ridiculousness -  Tv Show - MTV Nederland|url=http://m.mtv.nl/shows/3111-dutch-ridiculousness|work=m.mtv.nl|date=}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{Flag|Italy}}\n| [[MTV (Italy)]]\n| ''Ridiculousness Italia''\n| 2016\u20132017\n|<ref>{{cite web|author=|title=Ridiculousness Italia -  Programma - MTV Italia|url=http://ondemand.mtv.it/serie-tv/ridiculousness-italia|work=ondemand.mtv.it|date=}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{Flag|Denmark}}\n| [[MTV Denmark]]\n| ''Ridiculousness Danmark''\n| 2017\u2013\n|<ref>{{cite web|author=|title=Ridiculousness kommer til Danmark|url=http://m.mtv.dk/nyheder/105145-ridiculousness-kommer-til-danmark|work=MTV.dk|date=}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{Flag|Canada}}\n| [[MTV Canada]]\n| ''It's Ridiculous''\n| 2012\u2013\n|\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{Flag|Middle East}}\n| [[Comedy Central Arabia]]\n| ''Ridiculousness Arabia''\n| 2017\u2013\n|\n|-\n|}\n\n==Specials==\nOn February 10 and 11, 2020, MTV aired two special themed episodes of Ridiculousness titled ''Grossness'' hosted by [[Nina Agdal]] which focus the grossest and most shocking videos and ''WTF!ness'' hosted by James Davis focus on internet videos that leave them uttering one phrase, \u201cWTF!\u201d<ref>{{cite web|url=https://popculture.com/tv-shows/2020/02/06/ridiculousness-set-air-two-special-themed-episodes-mtv-grossness-wtfness/|title=Ridiculousness Set to Air Two Special Themed Episodes on MTV|author=Kyle Phillippi|work=Pop Culture|date=February 7, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{official website|http://www.mtv.com/shows/ridiculousness/series.jhtml}}\n* {{IMDb title|1820166|Ridiculousness}}\n\n{{MTVNetwork Shows}}\n\n\n[[Category:Television series by Dickhouse Productions]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American comedy TV series}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Ridiculousness\n| image                    = Ridiculousness (TV series).jpg\n| genre                    = {{plainlist|\n* [[Clip show]]\n* [[Comedy]]\n}}\n| presenter                = {{plainlist|\n* [[Rob Dyrdek]]\n* [[Steelo Brim|Sterling \"Steelo\" Brim]]\n* [[Chanel West Coast]]\n}}  \n| theme_music_composer     = [[Mark Mothersbaugh]]\n| opentheme                = {{plainlist|\n* \"[[Uncontrollable Urge]]\"\n* created by [[Devo]]; performed by Rob Dyrdek\n}}\n| country                  = United States\n| language                 = English\n| num_seasons              = 17\n| num_episodes             = 492\n| list_episodes            = List of Ridiculousness episodes\n| executive_producer       = {{plainlist|\n* Christian Duguay\n* [[Jeff 